---
title: Fish and Chips with Tilapia, Dill Pickle Tartar Sauce, and Zucchini
description: Fish and chips is as quintessentially British as tea time, Union Jacks, and monarchy. But that doesn’t mean it’s too far out there for Yankee taste buds. With tilapia strips fried in a crisp, golden batter and thick potato wedges roasted until they’re toasty and brown, our version is really just a hearty seafood dinner. But to make sure it’s got a bit of variety, we’re adding tender roasted zucchini and a DIY tartar sauce.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/fish-and-chips-38b50a5c.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/fish-and-chips-8a812c09.pdf
cuisine: British
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/fish-and-chips-59ea1236450cfa71c81897f2
servings: 2
author: Sara Heilman
course: main course
nutrition:
  calories: 700 kcal
  fat: 37 g
  saturated fat: 7 g
  carbohydrates: 69 g
  sugar: 7 g
  protein: 38 g
  fiber: 9 g
  sodium: 1030 mg
time required: 40 minutes
---

Wash and dry all produce. Adjust rack to middle position and preheat oven to 450 degrees. Cut @Yukon Gold Potatoes{12%ounce} into ¼-inch-thick wedges. Cut @lemon{1} into wedges. Cut @dill pickle{1} lengthwise into quarters; finely chop one quarter. Halve @zucchini{1} crosswise, then cut each half lengthwise into eight wedges.

Toss potatoes on a #baking sheet{} with half the @fry seasoning{1%tablespoon}, a drizzle of @vegetable oil{2%tablespoon}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}. Roast in oven until tender and crisped, about ~{20%minutes}, tossing halfway through.

Cut @tilapia{11%ounce} lengthwise into 1-inch wide strips (you'll have about 6). Season all over with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Whisk @flour{1/2%cup}, @baking powder{1%teaspoon}, remaining fry seasoning, @cornstarch{2%tablespoon}, and 3/4 cup water in a #medium bowl{}. Season with salt and pepper. Add tilapia to bowl, one piece at a time, tossing to coat in batter.

Heat a thin layer of @vegetable oil{1%tablespoon} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat (we used 2 TBSP). Once oil is hot, remove tilapia from bowl, letting excess batter drip off, and add to pan. Cook until deeply golden and crisp, about ~{5%minutes} per side. Transfer to a #paper-towel-lined plate{} and immediately season with salt and pepper.

> Work in batches, taking care not to overcrowd the pan.

While fish cooks, combine chopped pickle, @sour cream{2%tablespoon}, and @mayonnaise{2%tablespoon} in a #small bowl{}. Stir in a squeeze or two of lemon (to taste). Season with salt and pepper. Once potatoes are done roasting, remove from baking sheet and set aside, covered, to keep warm. Heat broiler to high or increase oven temperature to 500 degrees.

Toss zucchini on same baking sheet with a drizzle of @vegetable oil{1%teaspoon}, salt, and pepper. Broil (or bake) until tender and browned, about ~{10%minutes}. Divide between plates, along with tilapia, potatoes, and pickle quarters (split one in half, unless they're too good to share). Serve with tartar sauce for dipping and lemon wedges for squeezing over.